Susan Saint James https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Susan_Saint_James 0 Susan Saint James (born Susan Jane Miller; August 14, 1946) is an American actress and activist, most widely known for her work in television during the 1960s, 1970s and 1980s, especially the detective series McMillan Wife (1971–1976) and the sitcom Kate Allie (1984–1989).
